uid4nps

Class PANOSApiConnector

  • java.lang.Object
    • uid4nps.PANOSApiConnector

  • public class PANOSApiConnector
extends java.lang.Object
    This class hosts all methods and fields needed to keep the API connection opened with the PANOS device After the constructor has initialized all fields, the consumer must call the startTimer(java.lang.String) before any call to sendUserIdMessage(java.lang.String)

    • Method Detail

      • checkConnection

        public void checkConnection()
                     throws java.net.ProtocolException
        Method to check the successful connection with the PANOS device First we check if we've been requested to giveUp (called the userid4nps.stop(java.lang.String[]) method in the main class). In such a case we just return. Otherwise we'll send the panosCheckCommand to the device to check if it produces a valid response.

        If there is any communications exception during the check, a 1 minute timer will be started to check the connection and the ready flag will be cleared

        If we get a valid response we cancel the timer and raise the ready flag

        Throws:
        java.net.ProtocolException

      • sendUserIdMessage

        public java.lang.String sendUserIdMessage(java.lang.String command)
                                   throws java.net.ProtocolException,
                                          java.io.UnsupportedEncodingException
        This method will send a correctly formated PANOS User-ID XML message to this PANOS device. We don't check the integrity of the message.

        In case of communications exception, we'll call startTimer(java.lang.String) to mark this device as non-functional and to start the checking timer

        Parameters:
        command - XML user-id message to be sent to this PANOS device
        Returns:
        the XML response message received from the PANOS device or null is case of communication error
        Throws:
        java.net.ProtocolException
        java.io.UnsupportedEncodingException

      • startTimer

        public void startTimer(java.lang.String reason)
        This method creates a 1 minute periodic timer to keep checking the connection with the PANOS device. The TimerTask field will call the checkConnection() method when triggered
        Parameters:
        reason - The message that will be logged at INFO level as the reason.
